---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "connectors — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>connectors</h1>
    <p><strong>what is a connector?</strong> a mechanical + electrical interface so parts can plug together.

    <!-- keep your existing table of families here -->
    <!-- … your JST/headers/USB etc. table … -->
    <p>ways to join boards, cables, and gizmos. choose by pitch, current, mating cycles, and locking.</p>

    <table class="cute">
      <thead><tr><th>family</th><th>pitch</th><th>use</th><th>notes</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>dupont jumpers</td><td>2.54 mm</td><td>breadboards, quick leads</td><td>friction fit only</td></tr>
        <tr><td>headers (pin rows)</td><td>2.54 mm</td><td>male/female rows</td><td>stackable, cheap</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>JST-XH</strong></td><td>2.50 mm</td><td>wires ↔ board</td><td>locking latch; libraries often say 2.54 mm; not breadboard-friendly</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>JST-PH</strong></td><td>2.00 mm</td><td>batteries, sensors</td><td>compact, locking</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>JST-SH</strong></td><td>1.00 mm</td><td>Qwiic/STEMMA QT</td><td>tiny; I²C harnesses</td></tr>
        <tr><td>USB-C recept.</td><td>~0.5 mm pins</td><td>data/power</td><td>needs ESD + CC resistors; careful footprinting</td></tr>
        <tr><td>barrel jack</td><td>5.5×2.1 mm</td><td>DC power</td><td>check polarity (+ center, usually)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="header vs JST: friction vs latch">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 120" width="100%" height="auto">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="520" height="120" rx="16" fill="var(--card)"/>
        <!-- header -->
        <rect x="40" y="30" width="120" height="60" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <g opacity=".8">
          <rect x="55" y="40" width="10" height="40" rx="2" fill="currentColor"/>
          <rect x="75" y="40" width="10" height="40" rx="2" fill="currentColor"/>
          <rect x="95" y="40" width="10" height="40" rx="2" fill="currentColor"/>
          <rect x="115" y="40" width="10" height="40" rx="2" fill="currentColor"/>
        </g>
        <text x="50" y="22" class="mono">2.54 mm header</text>

        <!-- JST housing with latch -->
        <rect x="300" y="30" width="120" height="60" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <rect x="300" y="30" width="20" height="20" rx="3" fill="currentColor" opacity=".2"/>
        <text x="300" y="22" class="mono">JST with latch</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h2>strain relief</h2>
    <p>tie-downs, cable glands, and hot-glue blobs save JST/Dupont from yanks. route cables along edges.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
